fm_tone_tool.set_fm_tone_algorithm.name: FM algorithm that determines how the four operators (C, A, B1, B2) are routed and interact

values.display: Algorithm 1: Classic 4-op stack (B2->B1->A->C). Most complex modulation.
Algorithm 2: Dual 2-op stacks (B2->B1, A->C). Two independent FM pairs.
Algorithm 3: Three modulators to one carrier (B2, B1, A all modulate C).
Algorithm 4: Y-shaped routing (B2->B1->C, A->C). Branched modulation.
Algorithm 5: Diamond configuration with complex cross-modulation.
Algorithm 6: Two carriers with shared modulators.
Algorithm 7: Parallel configuration with B2 modulating both B1 and A.
Algorithm 8: Four parallel carriers (additive synthesis, no FM).

fm_drum_tool.set_fm_drum_algorithm.name: FM algorithm that determines how the three operators are routed in the FM drum engine

values.display: Algorithm 1: Simple stack (B->A->C). Good for punchy kicks.
Algorithm 2: Parallel modulation (B->C, A->C). Versatile, good for snares.
Algorithm 3: Y-configuration. Complex modulation for metallic sounds.
Algorithm 4: Triangle configuration. Rich harmonics for toms.
Algorithm 5: Mixed routing. Balanced for general percussion.
Algorithm 6: Complex branching. Good for hi-hats and cymbals.
